    <string name="lesson_disc"> <b> Koch method </b> now regarded as the <b>fastest route</b> to morse code proficiency. \n
        The philosophy of the method is simple: You do not learn morse the same way you study and learn other subjects. \n
        Morse code is the translation between a stimulus (sound in our case) into a reaction (writing down the letter). \n
        Learning morse code is not a particularly conscious process, it is more like developing <b>reflexes</b>. \n
        Start off with two characters sent at <b>full speed</b> (first lesson). \n
        Write down each character as you identify it. Do this during a five minute session. \n
        If you have jotted down the characters with at least 90 percent success rate then will be added one more char. \n
        Do this until all characters have been processed. \n
